{
  "stem": "18581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Except that in-- in '39 and 1940, when Poland fell apart, and Lithuania, Latvia and Estonia tried to keep their neutrality, and everybody knew that they will not be able to.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the rest of them-- the [INAUDIBLE] were far apart and unable to help.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So then we knew that it would be either Hitler would occupy, or Russia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we-- we said, we rather be red than dead.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we did not know everything because there was a-- there were secret clauses.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one of the secret clauses was the division of the Baltic countries.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Which are the-- on the first-- in the first agreement, they're supposed to be divided, Latvia and Estonia to the Soviets, Lithuania to Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After a-- a week, Stalin changed his mind and he renegotiated the treaty.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And according to the new agreement, the-- Lithuania was also to be ceded to Russia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was mixed feelings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But many people, at the first gut feeling, were happy that it was the Russians and not the Germans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I speak of the Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Lithuanians, of course, grieved.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For them, it was the loss of their independence they-- they have regained from the czar after 127 years of Russian occupation of Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So for them, it was a tragedy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they viewed the throwing of flowers to the Russian soldiers and the approval by some people as treachery, from their point of view, as ungratefulness from the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, afterwards, of course, the Jews started to feel what Russia and what Russian rule really meant.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was a total change.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All the Hebrew schools were closed and made into Yiddish schools, state schools, or closed completely.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
